@node BUGS "ANSI-Draw ... BUGS!"

@{b}BUGS!@{ub}

I have found a bug that is quite annoying. I don't think it is my fault, it
has something to do with the gadtools.library.

Here is the problem:
The problem is a PALETTE_KIND gadget that show the current color selected.
I change the current color selected by using GT_SetGadgetAttrs(). I
change between the colors very rapidly (I don't think I have to change that
very fast, but the bug is caught easier that way). I have enclosed the
window pointer to GT_SetGadgetAttrs() so that screen-rendering will be done
for the new choice. If I now, while the colors are changing, try to grab
a window, pull down a menu or something else that has to do with the basic
windowrendering the computer will totaly lock itself. The only thing to do
is to reboot. This bug does not appear if I do not enclose the windowpointer
(which is the same as that the PALETTE_KIND gadget only will be updated
internaly, not on the screen). I don't think this bug has something to do
with ANSI-Draw, because I have tested, and found, the same bug by rewriting
an example from the RKRM. I have come to the conclusion that the bug must
be in the rendering of the PALETTE_KIND gadget (I have tested the
CHECKMARK_KIND gadget and it didn't have this bug) in gadtools.library.

Why am I now telling you about this bug?

Well there are two answers to that. Number one is that you might be somewhat
carefull (which means not pulling down menus or moving windows etc.) when
using ARexx scripts that change the colors very often. Number two is that
I seek for help among you users how to solve this bug. I've tried all from
Forbid() to SetTaskPri(127) but nothing seems to work. I would like you to
try this bug out to see if it is only on my machine this problem appears.

If you have anything at all to tell me about this bug or anything at all
to say to me, please @{" EMail " link Author} me.

BTW, I use gadtools.library 39.356.



@endnode



