@node ARexxCommands "ANSI-Draw ... ARexxCommands"

   @{" DRAW     " link ARexx_DRAW}
   @{" GO       " link ARexx_GO}
   @{" SET      " link ARexx_SET}
   @{" UNSET    " link ARexx_UNSET}
   @{" LOCK     " link ARexx_LOCK}
   @{" UNLOCK   " link ARexx_UNLOCK}
   @{" QUERY    " link ARexx_QUERY}

@endnode

@node ARexx_GO "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: GO"

@{b}
command     option            argument    description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
GO          TOP                           Move cursor to top row.
            BOTTOM                        Move cursor to bottom row.
            ROW               #           Move cursor to row #.
            COLUMN            #           Move cursor to column #.
            UP                            Move cursor up.
            DOWN                          Move cursor down.
            BACKWARD                      Moves cursor backward.
            FOREWARD                      Moves cursor foreward.
@endnode

@node ARexx_DRAW "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: DRAW"

@{b}
command     option            argument    description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
DRAW        CHARACTER         #           Types character with ASCII-Code #
                                          (as if typed on keyboard).
            SCREEN                        Redraws the screen.
@endnode

@node ARexx_SET "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: SET"

@{b}
command     option            argument    description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
SET         WRITEMODE         'OVERWRITE' Sets overwrite mode.
                              'INSERT'    Sets insert mode.
            STYLE_ITALIC                  Turn italic on.
            STYLE_BOLD                    Turn bold on.
            STYLE_UNDERLINE               Turn underline on.
            STYLE_REVERSE                 Turn reverse on.
            FILTER_FOREGROUND             Turn foreground filter on.
            FILTER_BACKGROUND             Turn background filter on.
            FILTER_TEXT                   Turn text filter on.
            FILTER_STYLE                  Turn style filter on.
            COLOR_FOREGROUND  #           Sets foreground color with index #.
            COLOR_BACKGROUND  #           Sets background color with index #.
            SNAP_ATTRIBUTE                Sets same attributes as below
                                          cursor.
            BUFFER_CHANGED                Sets the "buffer changed" flag.
                                          (drawing-commands does this
                                          automaticly).
@endnode

@node ARexx_UNSET "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: UNSET"

@{b}
command     option            argument    description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
UNSET       STYLE_ITALIC                  Turn italic off.
            STYLE_BOLD                    Turn bold off.
            STYLE_UNDERLINE               Turn underline off.
            STYLE_REVERSE                 Turn reverse off.
            FILTER_FOREGROUND             Turn foreground filter off.
            FILTER_BACKGROUND             Turn background filter off.
            FILTER_TEXT                   Turn text filter off.
            FILTER_STYLE                  Turn style filter off.
            BUFFER_CHANGED                Sets the "buffer not changed" flag.
@endnode


@node ARexx_LOCK "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: LOCK"

@{b}
command     option            argument    description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
LOCK        INPUT                         Disables user input. 
            OUTPUT                        Disables screen output
@endnode


@node ARexx_UNLOCK "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: UNLOCK"

@{b}
command     option            argument    description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
UNLOCK      INPUT                         Enables user input.  
            OUTPUT                        Enables screen output
@endnode


@node ARexx_QUERY "ANSI-DRAW ... ARexxCommands: QUERY"

@{b}
command     option                  description
----------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
QUERY       ROW                     Returns XCursor position  
            COLUMN                  Returns YCursor position 
            BUFFER_ROWS             Returns no. rows in buffer
            SCREEN_ROWS             Returns no. max-rows on screen
            SCREEN_TOPROW           Returns topmost row nr. on screen
            CHARACTER               Returns the ASCII-code for the
                                    character underneath the cursor.
            COLOR_FOREGROUND        Returns the foregroundcolor index
                                    nr underneath the cursor.
            COLOR_BACKGROUND        Returns the backgroundcolor index
                                    nr underneath the cursor.
            STYLE_ITALIC            Returns 1 if italic is on under cursor,
                                    0 otherwise.
            STYLE_BOLD              Returns 1 if bold is on under cursor, 0
                                    otherwise.
            STYLE_UNDERLINE         Returns 1 if unserline is on under
                                    cursor, 0 otherwise.
            STYLE_REVERSE           Returns 1 if reverse is on under cursor,
                                    0 otherwise.
            FILTER_BACKGROUND       Returns 1 if background filter is on, 0
                                    otherwise.
            FILTER_FOREGROUND       Returns 1 if foreground filter is on, 0
                                    otherwise.
            FILTER_TEXT             Returns 1 if text filter is on, 0
                                    otherwise.
            FILTER_STYLE            Returns 1 if style filter is on, 0
                                    otherwise.
            BLOCK_STARTX            Returns start column of marked block.
            BLOCK_STARTY            Returns start row of marked block.
            BLOCK_STOPX             Returns stop column of marked block.
            BLOCK_STOPY             Returns stop row of marked block.
@endnode



@node GeneralInfo "ANSI-Draw ... General info"
I will now go through some general information and some hints on how to use
this program.

First of all I want to explain the use of @{u}filters@{uu}.
All the editing is based on the use of the four different filters: 

               Foreground, Background, Text and Style

Say for example that you've made an extreamly nice looking background area
using the backgroundcolors. Now you want to type some text on top of your
nice background but you still want to keep your background intact. This is
where the filters come in. All you have to do is to turn the background
filter off (unmark the "Backgr." option in the editwindow) and keep the
text, style and foreground filter on. Now you can freely type your text
ontop of your background without any risk of damaging it.

To reverse the order, say that you've typed a long text and want to color
it. Now you simply unmark the text and style filters and mark the
foreground and background filters. Now select a nice background and
foreground color and step out in the text on a word. Press space a few
times. What you now will recognize is that the text still will be intact but
the colors have changed. No harm will be made to the text.

At first all this use of filters might seem complicated to you, but I
promise you that when you get the hang of it you can't be without it.

Almost all of the built-in functions make use of the filters.

Somthing else to keep in mind using this program is that it is not a word-
processor. What I mean with that is that if you type text in insertmode, all
text that is pushed beyond column 80 can be considered lost.

@{u}Some hints for cursor movement@{uu}
The cursor can be placed on the screen by pointing with the mouse pressing
the left mousebutton. Other cursor movements are:

 @{b}Arrowkeys@{ub}           will move the cursor one step in respectivly direction.

 @{b}SHIFT + Left arrow@{ub}  will step to the end of the previous word.

 @{b}SHIFT + Right arrow@{ub} will step the the beginning of the next word.

 @{b}SHIFT + Down arrow@{ub}  will step one page down.

 @{b}SHIFT + Up arrow@{ub}    will step one page up.

  @{b}CTRL + Left arrow@{ub}  will step to column 80.

  @{b}CTRL + Right arrow@{ub} will step to column 1.

  @{b}CTRL + Up arrow@{ub}    will step to row 1.

  @{b}CTRL + Down arrow@{ub}  will step to last row.

  @{b} ALT + Left arrow@{ub}  will step to previous foreground color

  @{b} ALT + Right arrow@{ub} will step to next foreground color

  @{b} ALT + Up arrow@{ub}    will step to next background color

  @{b} ALT + Down arrow@{ub}  will step to previous background color

@{b} SHIFT + Delete@{ub}      will remove characters till end of line

@{b} SHIFT + Backspace@{ub}   will remove characters till beginning of line

@endnode


